On December 4, 2018, the President signed into law the "Frank LoBiondo Coast Guard Authorization Act of 2018" (S. 140). This act authorizes appropriations for the United States Coast Guard and the Federal Maritime Commission for the fiscal year 2019. It also reauthorizes the Department of Commerce's National Oceanic and Atmospheric Administration's hydrographic services program through fiscal year 2023. Additionally, the act modifies the regulation of vessel incidental discharge and ballast water.